160//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
161Ztring Mpeg4_Encoded_Library(int32u Vendor)
162{
163 switch (Vendor)
164 {
165 case 0x33495658 : return __T("3ivX"); //3IVX
166 case 0x6170706C : return __T("Apple QuickTime"); //appl
167 case 0x6E696B6F : return __T("Nikon"); //niko
168 case 0x6F6C796D : return __T("Olympus"); //olym
169 case 0x6F6D6E65 : return __T("Omneon"); //omne
170 default: return Ztring().From_CC4(Vendor);
171 }
172}
173
174//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
175Ztring Mpeg4_Language_Apple(int16u Language)
176{
177 switch (Language)
178 {
179 case 0 : return __T("en");
180 case 1 : return __T("fr");
181 case 2 : return __T("de");
182 case 6 : return __T("es");
183 default: return Ztring::ToZtring(Language);
184 }
185}

251//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
252void File_Mpeg4::Streams_Accept()
253{
254 if (!IsSub)
255 {
256 /*bool IsDashMpd=false;
257 for (size_t Pos=0; pos<ftyps
258 TestContinuousFileNames();*/
259 }
260
261 if (!IsSub && MajorBrand==0x6A703220) //"jp2 "
262 {
263 TestContinuousFileNames();
264
265 Stream_Prepare((Config->File_Names.size()>1 || Config->File_IsReferenced_Get())?Stream_Video:Stream_Image);
266 if (StreamKind_Last==Stream_Video)
267 Fill(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_FrameCount, Config->File_Names.size());
268 }
269
270 //Configuration
271 Buffer_MaximumSize=64*1024*1024; //Some big frames are possible (e.g YUV 4:2:2 10 bits 1080p)
272 File_Buffer_Size_Hint_Pointer=Config->File_Buffer_Size_Hint_Pointer_Get();
273}

275//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
276void File_Mpeg4::Streams_Finish()
277{
278 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_REFERENCES_YES) && MEDIAINFO_NEXTPACKET
279 //Locators only
280 if (ReferenceFiles_IsParsing)
281 {
282 ReferenceFiles->ParseReferences();
283 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
284 if (Config->Demux_EventWasSent)
285 return;
286 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
287
288 Streams_Finish_CommercialNames();
289 return;
290 }
291 #endif //defined(MEDIAINFO_REFERENCES_YES) && MEDIAINFO_NEXTPACKET
292
293 //Final Cut EIA-608 format
294 if (Retrieve(Stream_General, 0, General_Format)==__T("Final Cut EIA-608"))
295 {
296 for (streams::iterator Stream=Streams.begin(); Stream!=Streams.end(); ++Stream)
297 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<Streams[(int32u)Element_Code].Parsers.size(); Pos++)
298 {
299 Stream->second.Parsers[Pos]->Finish();
300 if (Stream->second.Parsers[Pos]->Count_Get(Stream_Text))
301 {
302 Stream_Prepare(Stream_Text);
303 Fill(Stream_Text, StreamPos_Last, Text_ID, Stream->first==1?"608-1":"608-2");
304 Fill(Stream_Text, StreamPos_Last, "MuxingMode", __T("Final Cut"), Unlimited);
305 Merge(*Stream->second.Parsers[Pos], Stream_Text, 0, StreamPos_Last);
306 }
307
308 //Law rating
309 Ztring LawRating=Stream->second.Parsers[Pos]->Retrieve(Stream_General, 0, General_LawRating);
310 if (!LawRating.empty())
311 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_LawRating, LawRating, true);
312 Ztring Title=Stream->second.Parsers[Pos]->Retrieve(Stream_General, 0, General_Title);
313 if (!Title.empty() && Retrieve(Stream_General, 0, General_Title).empty())
314 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_Title, Title);
315 }
316
317 return;
318 }
319
320 Fill_Flush();
321 int64u File_Size_Total=File_Size;
322
323 //TimeCode
324 for (streams::iterator Temp=Streams.begin(); Temp!=Streams.end(); ++Temp)
325 if (Temp->second.TimeCode)
326 TimeCode_Associate(Temp->first);
327
328 //For each stream
329 streams::iterator Temp=Streams.begin();
330 while (Temp!=Streams.end())
331 {
332 //Preparing
333 StreamKind_Last=Temp->second.StreamKind;
334 StreamPos_Last=Temp->second.StreamPos;
335
336 if (StreamKind_Last==Stream_Max && Temp->second.hdlr_SubType)
337 {
338 Stream_Prepare(Stream_Other);
339 Fill(Stream_Other, StreamPos_Last, Other_Type, Ztring().From_CC4(Temp->second.hdlr_SubType));
340 }
341
342 //if (Temp->second.stsz_StreamSize)
343 // Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, Fill_Parameter(StreamKind_Last, Generic_StreamSize), Temp->second.stsz_StreamSize);
344
345 //flags and references
346 if (StreamKind_Last != Stream_Menu)
347 {
348 Ztring TempString;
349 std::vector<int32u>::iterator TrackID;
350 if (StreamKind_Last == Stream_Text)
351 {
352 std::vector<int32u> TrackIDs = Temp->second.SubtitleFor;
353 for (TrackID = Temp->second.Forced.begin(); TrackID != Temp->second.Forced.end(); ++TrackID)
354 {
355 for (std::vector<int32u>::iterator TrackID2 = Streams[*TrackID].SubtitleFor.begin(); TrackID2 != Streams[*TrackID].SubtitleFor.end(); ++TrackID2)
356 {
357 TrackIDs.push_back(*TrackID2);
358 }
359 }
360 for (TrackID = Temp->second.ForcedFor.begin(); TrackID != Temp->second.ForcedFor.end(); ++TrackID)
361 {
362 for (std::vector<int32u>::iterator TrackID2 = Streams[*TrackID].SubtitleFor.begin(); TrackID2 != Streams[*TrackID].SubtitleFor.end(); ++TrackID2)
363 {
364 TrackIDs.push_back(*TrackID2);
365 }
366 }
367 sort (TrackIDs.begin(), TrackIDs.end());
368 TrackIDs.erase( unique(TrackIDs.begin(), TrackIDs.end()), TrackIDs.end());
369 for (std::vector<int32u>::iterator TrackID = TrackIDs.begin(); TrackID != TrackIDs.end(); ++TrackID)
370 {
371 if (TempString.size()) TempString.append(__T(","));
372 TempString.append(Ztring().From_Number(*TrackID));
373 }
374 if (TempString.size())
375 {
376 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Subtitles For", TempString.To_Local().c_str());
377 TempString.clear();
378 }
379 }
380 if (Temp->second.IsExcluded)
381 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Default", "Excluded");
382 else
383 {
384 if (Temp->second.IsEnabled)
385 {
386 if (!Retrieve(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "AlternateGroup").empty()) // Redundant information if there is not alternate group
387 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Default", "Yes");
388 }
389 else
390 {
391 for (TrackID = Temp->second.FallBackTo.begin(); TrackID != Temp->second.FallBackTo.end(); ++TrackID)
392 {
393 if (Streams[*TrackID].IsEnabled)
394 {
395 if (TempString.size()) TempString.append(__T(" ,"));
396 else TempString=__T("Inherited From: ");
397 TempString.append(Ztring().From_Number(*TrackID));
398 }
399 }
400 for (TrackID = Temp->second.FallBackFrom.begin(); TrackID != Temp->second.FallBackFrom.end(); ++TrackID)
401 {
402 if (Streams[*TrackID].IsEnabled)
403 {
404 if (TempString.size()) TempString.append(__T(" ,"));
405 else TempString=__T("Inherited From: ");
406 TempString.append(Ztring().From_Number(*TrackID));
407 }
408 }
409 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Default", TempString.size()?TempString.To_Local().c_str():"No");
410 TempString.clear();
411 }
412 }
413 if (StreamKind_Last == Stream_Text)
414 {
415 if (Temp->second.HasForcedSamples)
416 {
417 if (Temp->second.AllForcedSamples)
418 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Forced", "Yes");
419 else
420 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Forced", "Mixed");
421 if (Temp->second.ForcedFor.size())
422 {
423 for (TrackID = Temp->second.ForcedFor.begin(); TrackID != Temp->second.ForcedFor.end(); ++TrackID)
424 {
425 if (TempString.size()) TempString.append(__T(","));
426 TempString.append(Ztring().From_Number(*TrackID));
427 }
428 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Full Alternative", TempString.To_Local().c_str());
429 TempString.clear();
430 }
431 }
432 else
433 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Forced", "No");
434 if (Temp->second.Forced.size())
435 {
436 for (TrackID = Temp->second.Forced.begin(); TrackID != Temp->second.Forced.end(); ++TrackID)
437 {
438 if (TempString.size()) TempString.append(__T(","));
439 TempString.append(Ztring().From_Number(*TrackID));
440 }
441 if (TempString.size()) Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Forced Alternative", TempString.To_Local().c_str());
442 TempString.clear();
443 }
444 }
445 if (StreamKind_Last == Stream_Audio)
446 {
447 if (Temp->second.FallBackTo.size())
448 {
449 for (TrackID = Temp->second.FallBackTo.begin(); TrackID != Temp->second.FallBackTo.end(); ++TrackID)
450 {
451 if (TempString.size()) TempString.append(__T(","));
452 TempString.append(Ztring().From_Number(*TrackID));
453 }
454 if (TempString.size())
455 {
456 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Fallback To", TempString.To_Local().c_str());
457 TempString.clear();
458 }
459 }
460 if (Temp->second.FallBackFrom.size())
461 {
462 for (TrackID = Temp->second.FallBackFrom.begin(); TrackID != Temp->second.FallBackFrom.end(); ++TrackID)
463 {
464 if (TempString.size()) TempString.append(__T(","));
465 TempString.append(Ztring().From_Number(*TrackID));
466 }
467 if (TempString.size())
468 {
469 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Fallback From", TempString.To_Local().c_str());
470 TempString.clear();
471 }
472 }
473 if (Temp->second.Subtitle.size())
474 {
475 std::vector<int32u> TrackIDs = Temp->second.Subtitle;
476 for (TrackID = Temp->second.Subtitle.begin(); TrackID != Temp->second.Subtitle.end(); ++TrackID)
477 {
478 std::vector<int32u>::iterator TrackID2;
479 for (TrackID2 = Streams[*TrackID].Forced.begin(); TrackID2 != Streams[*TrackID].Forced.end(); ++TrackID2)
480 {
481 TrackIDs.push_back(*TrackID2);
482 }
483 for (TrackID2 = Streams[*TrackID].ForcedFor.begin(); TrackID2 != Streams[*TrackID].ForcedFor.end(); ++TrackID2)
484 {
485 TrackIDs.push_back(*TrackID2);
486 }
487 }
488 sort (TrackIDs.begin(), TrackIDs.end());
489 TrackIDs.erase( unique(TrackIDs.begin(), TrackIDs.end()), TrackIDs.end());
490 for (std::vector<int32u>::iterator TrackID = TrackIDs.begin(); TrackID != TrackIDs.end(); ++TrackID)
491 {
492 if (TempString.size()) TempString.append(__T(","));
493 TempString.append(Ztring().From_Number(*TrackID));
494 }
495 if (TempString.size())
496 {
497 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Subtitles", TempString.To_Local().c_str());
498 TempString.clear();
499 }
500 }
501 }
502 if (Temp->second.CC.size())
503 {
504 for (TrackID = Temp->second.CC.begin(); TrackID != Temp->second.CC.end(); ++TrackID)
505 {
506 if (TempString.size()) TempString.append(__T(","));
507 TempString.append(Ztring().From_Number(*TrackID));
508 }
509 if (TempString.size())
510 {
511 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Closed Captions", TempString.To_Local().c_str());
512 TempString.clear();
513 }
514 }
515 else if (Temp->second.CCFor.size())
516 {
517 for (TrackID = Temp->second.CCFor.begin(); TrackID != Temp->second.CCFor.end(); ++TrackID)
518 {
519 if (TempString.size()) TempString.append(__T(","));
520 TempString.append(Ztring().From_Number(*TrackID));
521 }
522 if (TempString.size())
523 {
524 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Closed Captions For", TempString.To_Local().c_str());
525 TempString.clear();
526 }
527 }
528 if (Temp->second.Chapters.size())
529 {
530 for (TrackID = Temp->second.Chapters.begin(); TrackID != Temp->second.Chapters.end(); ++TrackID)
531 {
532 if (TempString.size()) TempString.append(__T(","));
533 TempString.append(Ztring().From_Number(*TrackID));
534 }
535 if (TempString.size())
536 {
537 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Menus", TempString.To_Local().c_str());
538 TempString.clear();
539 }
540 }
541 }
542
543 if (Temp->second.ChaptersFor.size())
544 {
545 Ztring TempString;
546 std::vector<int32u>::iterator TrackID;
547 for (TrackID = Temp->second.ChaptersFor.begin(); TrackID != Temp->second.ChaptersFor.end(); ++TrackID)
548 {
549 if (TempString.size()) TempString.append(__T(","));
550 TempString.append(Ztring().From_Number(*TrackID));
551 }
552 if (TempString.size())
553 {
554 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Menu For", TempString.To_Local().c_str());
555 TempString.clear();
556 }
557 }
558
559 //Edit lists coherencies
560 if (Temp->second.edts.size()>1 && Temp->second.edts[0].Duration==Temp->second.tkhd_Duration)
561 {
562 bool Duplicates=true;
563 for (size_t Pos=1; Pos<Temp->second.edts.size(); Pos++)
564 if (Temp->second.edts[Pos-1].Delay!=Temp->second.edts[Pos].Delay || Temp->second.edts[Pos-1].Duration!=Temp->second.edts[Pos].Duration || Temp->second.edts[Pos-1].Rate!=Temp->second.edts[Pos].Rate)
565 Duplicates=false;
566 if (Duplicates)
567 Temp->second.edts.resize(1);
568 }
569
570 //Fragments
571 if (IsFragmented)
572 {
573 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, Fill_Parameter(StreamKind_Last, Generic_Duration), Temp->second.stts_Duration/((float)Temp->second.mdhd_TimeScale)*1000, 0, true);
574 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, Fill_Parameter(StreamKind_Last, Generic_FrameCount), Temp->second.stts_FrameCount, 10, true);
575 }
576
577 //Duration/StreamSize
578 if (moov_mvhd_TimeScale && Temp->second.TimeCode==NULL && Temp->second.mdhd_TimeScale)
579 {
580 Ztring Duration_stts_FirstFrame, Duration_stts_LastFrame;
581 if (Temp->second.stts_Duration_FirstFrame)
582 Duration_stts_FirstFrame.From_Number(((float32)(((int32s)Temp->second.stts_Duration_FirstFrame)-((int32s)Temp->second.stts[1].SampleDuration)))*1000/Temp->second.mdhd_TimeScale, 0); //The duration of the frame minus 1 normal frame duration
583 if (Temp->second.stts_Duration_LastFrame)
584 Duration_stts_LastFrame.From_Number(((float32)(((int32s)Temp->second.stts_Duration_LastFrame)-((int32s)Temp->second.stts[Temp->second.stts_Duration_FirstFrame?1:0].SampleDuration)))*1000/Temp->second.mdhd_TimeScale, 0); //The duration of the frame minus 1 normal frame duration
585
586 float32 Duration_tkhd_H=((float32)(Temp->second.tkhd_Duration+1))/moov_mvhd_TimeScale;
587 float32 Duration_tkhd_L=((float32)(Temp->second.tkhd_Duration-1))/moov_mvhd_TimeScale;
588 float32 Duration_stts=((float32)Temp->second.stts_Duration)/Temp->second.mdhd_TimeScale;
589 if (!IsFragmented && Duration_stts && !(Duration_stts>=Duration_tkhd_L && Duration_stts<=Duration_tkhd_H))
590 {
591 //There is a difference between media/stts atom and track atom
592 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Source_Duration", Duration_stts*1000, 0);
593 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Source_Duration_FirstFrame", Duration_stts_FirstFrame);
594 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Source_Duration_LastFrame", Duration_stts_LastFrame);
595 if (Temp->second.stts.size()!=1 || Temp->second.mdhd_TimeScale<100 || Temp->second.stts[0].SampleDuration!=1) //TODO: test PCM
596 if (Temp->second.stts_FrameCount)
597 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Source_FrameCount", Temp->second.stts_FrameCount);
598 if (Temp->second.stsz_StreamSize)
599 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Source_StreamSize", Temp->second.stsz_StreamSize);
600
601 //Calculating new properties based on track duration
602 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, Fill_Parameter(StreamKind_Last, Generic_Duration), ((float32)Temp->second.tkhd_Duration)/moov_mvhd_TimeScale*1000, 0, true);
603 //Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Duration_FirstFrame", Duration_stts_FirstFrame);
604 Clear(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Duration_LastFrame"); //TODO
605
606 int64u FrameCount;
607 if (Temp->second.stts_Min && Temp->second.stts_Min==Temp->second.stts_Max)
608 FrameCount=float64_int64s(((float64)Temp->second.tkhd_Duration)/moov_mvhd_TimeScale*Temp->second.mdhd_TimeScale/Temp->second.stts_Min);
609 else
610 {
611 FrameCount=0;
612 int64u Ticks_Max=float64_int64s(((float64)Temp->second.tkhd_Duration)/moov_mvhd_TimeScale*Temp->second.mdhd_TimeScale);
613 int64u Ticks=0;
614 for (size_t stts_Pos=0; stts_Pos<Temp->second.stts.size(); stts_Pos++)
615 {
616 int64u Ticks_Complete = (int64u)Temp->second.stts[stts_Pos].SampleCount * (int64u)Temp->second.stts[stts_Pos].SampleDuration;
617 if (Ticks+Ticks_Complete>=Ticks_Max)
618 {
619 if (Temp->second.stts[stts_Pos].SampleDuration)
620 FrameCount+=float64_int64s(((float64)(Ticks_Max-Ticks))/Temp->second.stts[stts_Pos].SampleDuration);
621 break;
622 }
623 Ticks+=Ticks_Complete;
624 FrameCount+=Temp->second.stts[stts_Pos].SampleCount;
625 }
626 }
627 if (Temp->second.stts.size()!=1 || Temp->second.mdhd_TimeScale<100 || Temp->second.stts[0].SampleDuration!=1) //TODO: test PCM
628 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "FrameCount", FrameCount, 10, true);
629
630 if (Temp->second.stsz_Total.empty())
631 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "StreamSize", FrameCount*Temp->second.stsz_Sample_Size*Temp->second.stsz_Sample_Multiplier);
632 else if (FrameCount<=Temp->second.stsz_Total.size())
633 {
634 int64u StreamSize=0;
635 for (size_t stsz_Pos=0; stsz_Pos<FrameCount; stsz_Pos++)
636 StreamSize+=Temp->second.stsz_Total[stsz_Pos];
637 bool HasEncodedBitRate=!Retrieve(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "BitRate_Encoded").empty();
638 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, HasEncodedBitRate?"StreamSize_Encoded":"StreamSize", StreamSize);
639 }
640 }
641 else
642 {
643 //Normal
644 if (Retrieve(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, Fill_Parameter(StreamKind_Last, Generic_Duration)).empty())
645 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, Fill_Parameter(StreamKind_Last, Generic_Duration), Duration_stts*1000, 0);
646 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Duration_FirstFrame", Duration_stts_FirstFrame);
647 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Duration_LastFrame", Duration_stts_LastFrame);
648 if (Temp->second.stts.size()!=1 || Temp->second.mdhd_TimeScale<100 || Temp->second.stts[0].SampleDuration!=1) //TODO: test PCM
649 if (Retrieve(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, Fill_Parameter(StreamKind_Last, Generic_FrameCount)).empty() && Temp->second.stts_FrameCount)
650 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, Fill_Parameter(StreamKind_Last, Generic_FrameCount), Temp->second.stts_FrameCount);
651 bool HasPadding=(Temp->second.Parsers.size()==1 && !Temp->second.Parsers[0]->Retrieve(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "BitRate_Encoded").empty()) || (Temp->second.Parsers.size()==1 && Temp->second.Parsers[0]->Buffer_TotalBytes && ((float32)Temp->second.Parsers[0]->Buffer_PaddingBytes)/Temp->second.Parsers[0]->Buffer_TotalBytes>0.02);
652 if (Temp->second.stsz_StreamSize)
653 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, Fill_Parameter(StreamKind_Last, HasPadding?Generic_StreamSize_Encoded:Generic_StreamSize), Temp->second.stsz_StreamSize);
654 }
655 }
656
657 //Edit Lists
658 float64 Delay=0;
659 switch (Temp->second.edts.size())
660 {
661 case 0 :
662 break;
663 case 1 :
664 if (Temp->second.edts[0].Duration==Temp->second.tkhd_Duration && Temp->second.edts[0].Rate==0x00010000 && moov_mvhd_TimeScale)
665 {
666 Delay=Temp->second.edts[0].Delay;
667 Delay=-Delay;
668 if (Temp->second.mdhd_TimeScale)
669 Delay/=Temp->second.mdhd_TimeScale; //In seconds
670 }
671 break;
672 case 2 :
673 if (Temp->second.edts[0].Delay==(int32u)-1 && Temp->second.edts[0].Duration+Temp->second.edts[1].Duration==Temp->second.tkhd_Duration && Temp->second.edts[0].Rate==0x00010000 && Temp->second.edts[1].Rate==0x00010000 && moov_mvhd_TimeScale)
674 {
675 Delay=Temp->second.edts[0].Duration;
676 Temp->second.tkhd_Duration-=float64_int64s(Delay);
677 Delay/=moov_mvhd_TimeScale; //In seconds
678 }
679 break;
680 default:
681 break; //TODO: handle more complex Edit Lists
682 }
683 if (Delay && !Retrieve(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Source_Duration").empty())
684 {
685 Delay+=Retrieve(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, Fill_Parameter(StreamKind_Last, Generic_Delay)).To_float64()/1000; //TODO: use TimeCode value directly instead of the rounded value
686 if (!Retrieve(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, Fill_Parameter(StreamKind_Last, Generic_Delay_Source)).empty() && Retrieve(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, Fill_Parameter(StreamKind_Last, Generic_Delay_Source))!=__T("Container"))
687 {
688 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, Fill_Parameter(StreamKind_Last, Generic_Delay_Original), Retrieve(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, Fill_Parameter(StreamKind_Last, Generic_Delay)));
689 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, Fill_Parameter(StreamKind_Last, Generic_Delay_Original_Source), Retrieve(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, Fill_Parameter(StreamKind_Last, Generic_Delay_Source)));
690 }
691 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Source_Delay", Delay*1000, 0, true);
692 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Source_Delay_Source", "Container", Unlimited, true, true);
693 (*Stream_More)[StreamKind_Last][StreamPos_Last](Ztring().From_Local("Source_Delay"), Info_Options)=__T("N NT");
694 (*Stream_More)[StreamKind_Last][StreamPos_Last](Ztring().From_Local("Source_Delay_Source"), Info_Options)=__T("N NT");
695 }
696
697 if (StreamKind_Last==Stream_Video && Temp->second.TimeCode==NULL)
698 {
699 if (Temp->second.mdhd_TimeScale && Temp->second.stts_Min && Temp->second.stts_Max)
700 {
701 if (Temp->second.stts_Min==0 || Temp->second.stts_Max==0 || (Temp->second.stts_Min!=Temp->second.stts_Max && ((float)Temp->second.mdhd_TimeScale)/Temp->second.stts_Min-((float)Temp->second.mdhd_TimeScale)/Temp->second.stts_Max>=0.001))
702 {
703 if (Temp->second.stts_Max)
704 Fill(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_FrameRate_Minimum, ((float)Temp->second.mdhd_TimeScale)/Temp->second.stts_Max, 3, true);
705 if (Temp->second.stts_Min)
706 Fill(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_FrameRate_Maximum, ((float)Temp->second.mdhd_TimeScale)/Temp->second.stts_Min, 3, true);
707 if (Temp->second.stts_Duration)
708 Fill(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_FrameRate, ((float)Temp->second.stts_FrameCount)/Temp->second.stts_Duration*Temp->second.mdhd_TimeScale, 3, true);
709 Fill(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_FrameRate_Mode, "VFR", Unlimited, true, true);
710 }
711 else
712 {
713 Fill(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_FrameRate, ((float)Temp->second.mdhd_TimeScale)/Temp->second.stts_Max, 3, true);
714 Fill(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_FrameRate_Mode, "CFR", Unlimited, true, true);
715 }
716 }
717 }
718
719 //Coherency
720 if (!IsFragmented && Temp->second.stts_Duration!=Temp->second.mdhd_Duration && Temp->second.mdhd_TimeScale)
721 {
722 //There is a difference between media/mdhd atom and track atom
723 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "mdhd_Duration", ((float32)Temp->second.mdhd_Duration)/Temp->second.mdhd_TimeScale*1000, 0);
724 }
725
726 //When there are few frames, difficult to detect PCM
727 if (Temp->second.IsPcm && !Temp->second.Parsers.empty() && !Temp->second.Parsers[0]->Status[IsAccepted])
728 {
729 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<Temp->second.Parsers.size()-1; Pos++)
730 delete Temp->second.Parsers[Pos];
731 Temp->second.Parsers.erase(Temp->second.Parsers.begin(), Temp->second.Parsers.begin()+Temp->second.Parsers.size()-1);
732 Temp->second.Parsers[0]->Accept();
733 }
734
735 //Parser specific
736 if (Temp->second.Parsers.size()==1)
737 {
738 if (Config->ParseSpeed<=1.0)
739 {
740 Fill(Temp->second.Parsers[0]);
741 Temp->second.Parsers[0]->Open_Buffer_Unsynch();
742 }

744 //Finalizing and Merging
745 Finish(Temp->second.Parsers[0]);

750 if (Target->second.StreamKind!=Stream_General)
751 Merge(*Temp->second.Parsers[0], Target->second.StreamKind, 0, Target->second.StreamPos);
752 }
753 else
754 {

756 Ztring FrameRate_Temp, FrameRate_Mode_Temp, Duration_Temp, Delay_Temp;

775 Clear(Stream_Video, StreamKind_Last, Video_Width);

778 //Special case - Multiple sub-streams in a stream
779 if ((Temp->second.Parsers[0]->Retrieve(Stream_General, 0, General_Format)==__T("ChannelGrouping") && Temp->second.Parsers[0]->Count_Get(Stream_Audio))
780 || Temp->second.Parsers[0]->Retrieve(Stream_General, 0, General_Format)==__T("Final Cut EIA-608")

840 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<StreamSave.size(); Pos++)

847 if (!LawRating.empty())

850 if (!Title.empty() && Retrieve(Stream_General, 0, General_Title).empty())
851 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_Title, Title);
852 }

854 {
855 //Temp->second.Parsers[0]->Clear(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Delay"); //DV TimeCode is removed

857 size_t New_Count=Temp->second.Parsers[0]->Count_Get(StreamKind_Last);

859 ZtringList StreamSave;

876
877 streams::iterator NextStream=Temp;
878 ++NextStream;
879 while (NextStream!=Streams.end())
880 {
881 if (NextStream->second.StreamKind== StreamKind_Last)
882 NextStream->second.StreamPos++;
883 ++NextStream;
884 }

886 Merge(*Temp->second.Parsers[0], StreamKind_Last, Parser_StreamPos, StreamPos_Last);

890 if (Parser_StreamPos)
891 {
892 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<StreamSave.size(); Pos++)
893 if (Retrieve(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, Pos).empty())
894 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, Pos, StreamSave[Pos]);
895 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<StreamMoreSave.size(); Pos++)
896 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, StreamMoreSave(Pos, 0).To_Local().c_str(), StreamMoreSave(Pos, 1));
897 }

900 //Law rating
901 Ztring LawRating=Temp->second.Parsers[0]->Retrieve(Stream_General, 0, General_LawRating);
902 if (!LawRating.empty())
903 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_LawRating, LawRating, true);
904 Ztring Title=Temp->second.Parsers[0]->Retrieve(Stream_General, 0, General_Title);
905 if (!Title.empty() && Retrieve(Stream_General, 0, General_Title).empty())
906 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_Title, Title);

987 Fill(Stream_Text, Pos, Text_ID, Retrieve(Stream_Video, Temp->second.StreamPos, Video_ID)+__T("-")+ID, true);
988 Fill(Stream_Text, Pos, "Source", Retrieve(Stream_Video, Temp->second.StreamPos, "Source"));
989 Fill(Stream_Text, Pos, "Source_Info", Retrieve(Stream_Video, Temp->second.StreamPos, "Source_Info"));
990 }
991
992 StreamKind_Last=Temp->second.StreamKind;
993 StreamPos_Last=Temp->second.StreamPos;
994 }
995 }
996 }
997
998 //ScanOrder_StoredDisplayedInverted
999 // Priorizing https://developer.apple.com/library/mac/technotes/tn2162/_index.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/DTS40013070-CH1-TNTAG10-THE__FIEL__IMAGEDESCRIPTION_EXTENSION__FIELD_FRAME_INFORMATION
1000 /*
1001 switch (Temp->second.fiel_detail)
1002 {
1003 case 1 : // Separated fields, TFF
1004 case 6 : // Separated fields, BFF
1005 Fill(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_ScanOrder, "TFF", Unlimited, true, true);
1006 break;
1007 case 9 : // Interleaved fields, TFF
1008 case 14 : // Interleaved fields, BFF
1009 Fill(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_ScanOrder, "BFF", Unlimited, true, true);
1010 break;
1011 default : ;
1012 }
1013 */
1014
1015 //External file name specific
1016 if (Temp->second.MI && Temp->second.MI->Info)
1017 {
1018 //Preparing
1019 StreamKind_Last=Temp->second.StreamKind;
1020 StreamPos_Last=Temp->second.StreamPos;
1021
1022 //Hacks - Before
1023 Ztring CodecID=Retrieve(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, Fill_Parameter(StreamKind_Last, Generic_CodecID));
1024 Ztring Source=Retrieve(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Source");
1025 Ztring Source_Info=Retrieve(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Source_Info");
1026
1027 Merge(*Temp->second.MI->Info, Temp->second.StreamKind, 0, Temp->second.StreamPos);
1028 File_Size_Total+=Ztring(Temp->second.MI->Get(Stream_General, 0, General_FileSize)).To_int64u();
1029
1030 //Hacks - After
1031 if (CodecID!=Retrieve(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, Fill_Parameter(StreamKind_Last, Generic_CodecID)))
1032 {
1033 if (!CodecID.empty())
1034 CodecID+=__T(" / ");
1035 CodecID+=Retrieve(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, Fill_Parameter(StreamKind_Last, Generic_CodecID));
1036 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, Fill_Parameter(StreamKind_Last, Generic_CodecID), CodecID, true);
1037 }
1038 if (Source!=Retrieve(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Source"))
1039 {
1040 Ztring Source_Original=Retrieve(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Source");
1041 Ztring Source_Original_Info=Retrieve(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Source_Info");
1042 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Source", Source, true);
1043 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Source_Info", Source_Info, true);
1044 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Source_Original", Source_Original, true);
1045 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Source_Original_Info", Source_Original_Info, true);
1046 }
1047 if (StreamKind_Last==Stream_Audio
1048 && Retrieve(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_Format)!=__T("PCM")
1049 && !Retrieve(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_Channel_s__Original).empty())
1050 {
1051 Clear(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_Channel_s__Original);
1052 Fill(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_Channel_s_, 6, 10, true); //The PCM channel count is fake
1053 }
1054
1055 //Muxing Mode
1056 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "MuxingMode", Temp->second.MI->Get(Stream_General, 0, General_Format));
1057
1058 //Special case: DV with Audio or/and Text in the video stream
1059 if (StreamKind_Last==Stream_Video && Temp->second.MI->Info && (Temp->second.MI->Info->Count_Get(Stream_Audio) || Temp->second.MI->Info->Count_Get(Stream_Text)))
1060 {
1061 //Video and Audio are together
1062 size_t Audio_Count=Temp->second.MI->Info->Count_Get(Stream_Audio);
1063 for (size_t Audio_Pos=0; Audio_Pos<Audio_Count; Audio_Pos++)
1064 {
1065 Fill_Flush();
1066 Stream_Prepare(Stream_Audio);
1067 size_t Pos=Count_Get(Stream_Audio)-1;
1068 Merge(*Temp->second.MI->Info, Stream_Audio, Audio_Pos, StreamPos_Last);
1069 if (Retrieve(Stream_Audio, Pos, Audio_MuxingMode).empty())
1070 Fill(Stream_Audio, Pos, Audio_MuxingMode, Retrieve(Stream_Video, Temp->second.StreamPos, Video_Format), true);
1071 else
1072 Fill(Stream_Audio, Pos, Audio_MuxingMode, Retrieve(Stream_Video, Temp->second.StreamPos, Video_Format)+__T(" / ")+Retrieve(Stream_Audio, Pos, Audio_MuxingMode), true);
1073 Fill(Stream_Audio, Pos, Audio_MuxingMode_MoreInfo, __T("Muxed in Video #")+Ztring().From_Number(Temp->second.StreamPos+1));
1074 Fill(Stream_Audio, Pos, Audio_Duration, Retrieve(Stream_Video, Temp->second.StreamPos, Video_Duration), true);
1075 Fill(Stream_Audio, Pos, Audio_StreamSize_Encoded, 0); //Included in the DV stream size
1076 Ztring ID=Retrieve(Stream_Audio, Pos, Audio_ID);
1077 Fill(Stream_Audio, Pos, Audio_ID, Retrieve(Stream_Video, Temp->second.StreamPos, Video_ID)+__T("-")+ID, true);
1078 Fill(Stream_Audio, Pos, "Source", Retrieve(Stream_Video, Temp->second.StreamPos, "Source"));
1079 Fill(Stream_Audio, Pos, "Source_Info", Retrieve(Stream_Video, Temp->second.StreamPos, "Source_Info"));
1080 }
1081
1082 //Video and Text are together
1083 size_t Text_Count=Temp->second.MI->Info->Count_Get(Stream_Text);
1084 for (size_t Text_Pos=0; Text_Pos<Text_Count; Text_Pos++)
1085 {
1086 Fill_Flush();
1087 Stream_Prepare(Stream_Text);
1088 size_t Pos=Count_Get(Stream_Text)-1;
1089 Merge(*Temp->second.MI->Info, Stream_Text, Text_Pos, StreamPos_Last);
1090 if (Retrieve(Stream_Text, Pos, Text_MuxingMode).empty())
1091 Fill(Stream_Text, Pos, Text_MuxingMode, Retrieve(Stream_Video, Temp->second.StreamPos, Video_Format), true);
1092 else
1093 Fill(Stream_Text, Pos, Text_MuxingMode, Retrieve(Stream_Video, Temp->second.StreamPos, Video_Format)+__T(" / ")+Retrieve(Stream_Text, Pos, Text_MuxingMode), true);
1094 Fill(Stream_Text, Pos, Text_MuxingMode_MoreInfo, __T("Muxed in Video #")+Ztring().From_Number(Temp->second.StreamPos+1));
1095 Fill(Stream_Text, Pos, Text_Duration, Retrieve(Stream_Video, Temp->second.StreamPos, Video_Duration));
1096 Fill(Stream_Text, Pos, Text_StreamSize_Encoded, 0); //Included in the DV stream size
1097 Ztring ID=Retrieve(Stream_Text, Pos, Text_ID);
1098 Fill(Stream_Text, Pos, Text_ID, Retrieve(Stream_Video, Temp->second.StreamPos, Video_ID)+__T("-")+ID, true);
1099 Fill(Stream_Text, Pos, "Source", Retrieve(Stream_Video, Temp->second.StreamPos, "Source"));
1100 Fill(Stream_Text, Pos, "Source_Info", Retrieve(Stream_Video, Temp->second.StreamPos, "Source_Info"));
1101 }
1102 }
1103 }
1104
1105 //Aperture size
1106 if (Temp->second.CleanAperture_Width)
1107 {
1108 Fill(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, "Width_CleanAperture", Temp->second.CleanAperture_Width, 0, true);
1109 Fill(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, "Height_CleanAperture", Temp->second.CleanAperture_Height, 0, true);
1110 Fill(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, "PixelAspectRatio_CleanAperture", Temp->second.CleanAperture_PixelAspectRatio, 3, true);
1111 }
1112
1113 //Special case: QuickTime files and Stereo streams, there is a default value in QuickTime player, a QuickTime "standard"?
1114 if (StreamKind_Last==Stream_Audio
1115 && Retrieve(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_Channel_s_)==__T("2")
1116 && Retrieve(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_ChannelLayout).empty()
1117 && Retrieve(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_ChannelPositions).empty()
1118 && Retrieve(Stream_General, 0, General_Format_Profile)==__T("QuickTime"))
1119 {
1120 Fill(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_ChannelPositions, Mpeg4_chan(101));
1121 Fill(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_ChannelLayout, Mpeg4_chan_Layout(101));
1122 }
1123
1124 //Bitrate Mode
1125 if (Retrieve(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "BitRate_Mode").empty())
1126 {
1127 if (Temp->second.stss.empty() && Temp->second.stss.size()!=Temp->second.stsz_Total.size() && !IsFragmented)
1128 {
1129 int64u Size_Min=(int64u)-1, Size_Max=0;
1130 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<Temp->second.stsz_Total.size(); Pos++)
1131 {
1132 if (Temp->second.stsz_Total[Pos]<Size_Min)
1133 Size_Min=Temp->second.stsz_Total[Pos];
1134 if (Temp->second.stsz_Total[Pos]>Size_Max)
1135 Size_Max=Temp->second.stsz_Total[Pos];
1136 }
1137
1138 if (Size_Min*(1.005+0.005)<Size_Max)
1139 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "BitRate_Mode", "VBR");
1140 else
1141 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "BitRate_Mode", "CBR");
1142 }
1143 else
1144 {
1145 //TODO: compute Bit rate mode from stsz and stss (in order to compute per GOP instead of per frame)
1146 }
1147 }
1148
1149 for (std::map<string, Ztring>::iterator Info=Temp->second.Infos.begin(); Info!=Temp->second.Infos.end(); ++Info)
1150 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, Info->first.c_str(), Info->second);
1151
1152 ++Temp;
1153 }
1154 if (Vendor!=0x00000000 && Vendor!=0xFFFFFFFF)
1155 {
1156 Ztring VendorS=Mpeg4_Encoded_Library(Vendor);
1157 if (!Vendor_Version.empty())
1158 {
1159 VendorS+=__T(' ');
1160 VendorS+=Vendor_Version;
1161 }
1162 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_Encoded_Library, VendorS);
1163 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_Encoded_Library_Name, Mpeg4_Encoded_Library(Vendor));
1164 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_Encoded_Library_Version, Vendor_Version);
1165 }
1166
1167 if (File_Size_Total!=File_Size)
1168 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_FileSize, File_Size_Total, 10, true);
1169 if (Count_Get(Stream_Video)==0 && Count_Get(Stream_Image)==0 && Count_Get(Stream_Audio)>0)
1170 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_InternetMediaType, "audio/mp4", Unlimited, true, true);
1171
1172 //Parsing sequence files
1173 #ifdef MEDIAINFO_REFERENCES_YES
1174 for (streams::iterator Stream=Streams.begin(); Stream!=Streams.end(); ++Stream)
1175 if (!Stream->second.File_Name.empty())
1176 {
1177 if (ReferenceFiles==NULL)
1178 ReferenceFiles=new File__ReferenceFilesHelper(this, Config);
1179
1180 sequence* Sequence=new sequence;
1181 Sequence->AddFileName(Stream->second.File_Name);
1182 Sequence->StreamKind=Stream->second.StreamKind;
1183 Sequence->StreamPos=Stream->second.StreamPos;
1184 Sequence->StreamID=Retrieve(Stream->second.StreamKind, Stream->second.StreamPos, General_ID).To_int64u();
1185 if (Stream->second.StreamKind==Stream_Video)
1186 {
1187 Sequence->FrameRate_Set(Retrieve(Stream_Video, Stream->second.StreamPos, Video_FrameRate).To_float64());
1188
1189 #if MEDIAINFO_IBIUSAGE
1190 for (size_t stss_Pos=0; stss_Pos<Stream->second.stss.size(); stss_Pos++)
1191 {
1192 int64u Value=Stream->second.stss[stss_Pos];
1193
1194 //Searching the corresponding stco
1195 std::vector<stream::stsc_struct>::iterator Stsc=Stream->second.stsc.begin();
1196 int64u SamplePos=0;
1197 for (; Stsc!=Stream->second.stsc.end(); ++Stsc)
1198 {
1199 std::vector<stream::stsc_struct>::iterator Stsc_Next=Stsc; ++Stsc_Next;
1200 int64u CountOfSamples = ((Stsc_Next == Stream->second.stsc.end() ? ((int64u)Stream->second.stco.size()) : ((int64u)Stsc_Next->FirstChunk)) - (int64u)Stsc->FirstChunk) * (int64u)Stsc->SamplesPerChunk;
1201 if (Stsc_Next!=Stream->second.stsc.end() && Value>=SamplePos+CountOfSamples)
1202 SamplePos+=CountOfSamples;
1203 else
1204 {
1205 int64u CountOfChunks=(Value-SamplePos)/Stsc->SamplesPerChunk;
1206 size_t stco_Pos=(size_t)(Stsc->FirstChunk-1+CountOfChunks); //-1 because first chunk is number 1
1207 if (stco_Pos<Stream->second.stco.size())
1208 {
1209 stream::stts_durations::iterator stts_Duration=Stream->second.stts_Durations.begin()+Stream->second.stts_Durations_Pos;
1210 ibi::stream::info IbiInfo;
1211 IbiInfo.StreamOffset=Stream->second.stco[stco_Pos];
1212 IbiInfo.FrameNumber=Value;
1213 IbiInfo.Dts=TimeCode_DtsOffset+(stts_Duration->DTS_Begin+(((int64u)stts_Duration->SampleDuration)*(Value-stts_Duration->Pos_Begin)))*1000000000/Stream->second.mdhd_TimeScale;
1214 Sequence->IbiStream.Add(IbiInfo);
1215 }
1216 }
1217 }
1218 }
1219 #endif //MEDIAINFO_IBIUSAGE
1220
1221 }
1222 ReferenceFiles->AddSequence(Sequence);
1223 }
1224
1225 if (ReferenceFiles)
1226 {
1227 ReferenceFiles->ParseReferences();
1228 #if MEDIAINFO_NEXTPACKET
1229 if (Config->NextPacket_Get() && ReferenceFiles && ReferenceFiles->Sequences_Size())
1230 {
1231 ReferenceFiles_IsParsing=true;
1232 return;
1233 }
1234 #endif //MEDIAINFO_NEXTPACKET
1235 }
1236 #endif //MEDIAINFO_REFERENCES_YES
1237
1238 //Commercial names
1239 Streams_Finish_CommercialNames();
1240}

1291
1292//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1293void File_Mpeg4::Read_Buffer_Unsynched()
1294{
1295 if (!IsSub && MajorBrand==0x6A703220) //"jp2 "
1296 return Read_Buffer_Unsynched_OneFramePerFile();
1297
1298 if (mdat_Pos.empty())
1299 {
1300 IsParsing_mdat=false;
1301 return;
1302 }
1303 mdat_Pos_Temp=&mdat_Pos[0];
1304 while (mdat_Pos_Temp!=mdat_Pos_Max && mdat_Pos_Temp->Offset<File_GoTo)
1305 mdat_Pos_Temp++;
1306 if (mdat_Pos_Temp!=mdat_Pos_Max && mdat_Pos_Temp->Offset>File_GoTo)
1307 mdat_Pos_Temp--; //Previous frame
1308 if (mdat_Pos_Temp==mdat_Pos_Max)
1309 {
1310 IsParsing_mdat=false;
1311 return;
1312 }
1313 IsParsing_mdat=true;
1314
1315 #if MEDIAINFO_SEEK
1316 //Searching the ID of the first stream to be demuxed
1317 std::map<int32u, stream>::iterator Next_Stream=Streams.end();
1318 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1319 size_t Next_Stream_Stco=(size_t)-1;
1320 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1321 for (std::map<int32u, stream>::iterator Stream=Streams.begin(); Stream!=Streams.end(); ++Stream)
1322 {
1323 for (size_t Stco_Pos=0; Stco_Pos<Stream->second.stco.size(); Stco_Pos++)
1324 if (Stream->second.stco[Stco_Pos]==mdat_Pos_Temp->Offset)
1325 {
1326 Next_Stream=Stream;
1327 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1328 Next_Stream_Stco=Stco_Pos;
1329 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1330 break;
1331 }
1332 if (Next_Stream!=Streams.end())
1333 break;
1334 }
1335 #endif //MEDIAINFO_SEEK
1336
1337 for (std::map<int32u, stream>::iterator Stream=Streams.begin(); Stream!=Streams.end(); ++Stream)
1338 {
1339 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<Stream->second.Parsers.size(); Pos++)
1340 Stream->second.Parsers[Pos]->Open_Buffer_Unsynch();
1341
1342 #if MEDIAINFO_SEEK && MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1343 //Searching the next position for this stream
1344 int64u StreamOffset=(int64u)-1;
1345 if (StreamOffset_Jump.empty() || File_GoTo==mdat_Pos[0].Offset)
1346 StreamOffset=mdat_Pos_Temp->Offset;
1347 else if (Next_Stream_Stco!=(size_t)-1)
1348 {
1349 //Searching the right place for this stream
1350 int64u StreamOffset_Temp=Next_Stream->second.stco[Next_Stream_Stco];
1351 std::map<int64u, int64u>::iterator StreamOffset_Jump_Temp;
1352 for (;;)
1353 {
1354 StreamOffset_Jump_Temp=StreamOffset_Jump.find(StreamOffset_Temp);
1355 if (StreamOffset_Jump_Temp==StreamOffset_Jump.end())
1356 break;
1357 if (Stream==Next_Stream)
1358 StreamOffset_Temp=StreamOffset_Jump_Temp->first;
1359 else
1360 {
1361 ++StreamOffset_Jump_Temp;
1362 if (StreamOffset_Jump_Temp==StreamOffset_Jump.end())
1363 break;
1364 StreamOffset_Temp=StreamOffset_Jump_Temp->second;
1365 }
1366
1367 if (!Stream->second.stco.empty() && StreamOffset_Temp>=Stream->second.stco[0] && StreamOffset_Temp<=Stream->second.stco[Stream->second.stco.size()-1])
1368 for (size_t Stco_Pos=0; Stco_Pos<Stream->second.stco.size(); Stco_Pos++)
1369 if (StreamOffset_Temp==Stream->second.stco[Stco_Pos])
1370 {
1371 StreamOffset=Stream->second.stco[Stco_Pos];
1372 break;
1373 }
1374
1375 if (StreamOffset!=(int64u)-1)
1376 break;
1377 }
1378 }
1379
1380 if (StreamOffset!=(int64u)-1)
1381 for (size_t stco_Pos=0; stco_Pos<Stream->second.stco.size(); stco_Pos++)
1382 if (Stream->second.stco[stco_Pos]>=StreamOffset)
1383 {
1384 //Searching the corresponding frame position
1385 std::vector<stream::stsc_struct>::iterator Stsc=Stream->second.stsc.begin();
1386 int64u SamplePos=0;
1387 for (; Stsc!=Stream->second.stsc.end(); ++Stsc)
1388 {
1389 std::vector<stream::stsc_struct>::iterator Stsc_Next=Stsc; ++Stsc_Next;
1390 if (Stsc_Next!=Stream->second.stsc.end() && stco_Pos+1>=Stsc_Next->FirstChunk)
1391 {
1392 int64u CountOfSamples = ((int64u)Stsc_Next->FirstChunk - (int64u)Stsc->FirstChunk) * (int64u)Stsc->SamplesPerChunk;
1393 SamplePos+=CountOfSamples;
1394 }
1395 else
1396 {
1397 int64u CountOfSamples = ((int64u)stco_Pos + 1 - (int64u)Stsc->FirstChunk) * (int64u)Stsc->SamplesPerChunk;
1398 SamplePos+=CountOfSamples;
1399
1400 Stream->second.stts_FramePos=SamplePos;
1401
1402 //Searching the corresponding duration block position
1403 for (stream::stts_durations::iterator Stts_Duration=Stream->second.stts_Durations.begin(); Stts_Duration!=Stream->second.stts_Durations.end(); ++Stts_Duration)
1404 if (SamplePos>=Stts_Duration->Pos_Begin && SamplePos<Stts_Duration->Pos_End)
1405 {
1406 Stream->second.stts_Durations_Pos=Stts_Duration-Stream->second.stts_Durations.begin();
1407 break;
1408 }
1409
1410 break;
1411 }
1412 }
1413
1414 break;
1415 }
1416
1417 if (Stream->second.Demux_Level&(1<<6))
1418 {
1419 Stream->second.Demux_Level|= (1<<7); //Add the flag, SPS/PPS must be sent
1420 Stream->second.Demux_Level&=~(1<<6); //In case of seek again, no need to do it again
1421 }
1422 #endif //MEDIAINFO_SEEK && MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1423 }
1424}
1425
1426//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1427#if MEDIAINFO_SEEK
1428size_t File_Mpeg4::Read_Buffer_Seek (size_t Method, int64u Value, int64u ID)
1429{
1430 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_REFERENCES_YES)
1431 if (ReferenceFiles)
1432 return ReferenceFiles->Seek(Method, Value, ID);
1433 #endif //defined(MEDIAINFO_REFERENCES_YES)
1434 if (!IsSub && MajorBrand==0x6A703220) //"jp2 "
1435 return Read_Buffer_Seek_OneFramePerFile(Method, Value, ID);
1436
1437 //Parsing
1438 switch (Method)
1439 {
1440 case 0 :
1441 if (Value==0)
1442 return Read_Buffer_Seek(3, 0, ID);
1443
1444 if (FirstMoovPos==(int64u)-1)
1445 return 6; //Internal error
1446
1447 if (Value>=LastMdatPos)
1448 {
1449 GoTo(File_Size);
1450 Open_Buffer_Unsynch();
1451 return 1;
1452 }
1453
1454 {
1455 //Looking for the minimal stream offset, for every video/audio/text stream
1456 int64u JumpTo=File_Size;
1457 for (std::map<int32u, stream>::iterator Stream=Streams.begin(); Stream!=Streams.end(); ++Stream)
1458 switch (Stream->second.StreamKind)
1459 {
1460 case Stream_Video :
1461 case Stream_Audio :
1462 case Stream_Text :
1463 {
1464 //Searching the corresponding chunk offset
1465 std::vector<int64u>::iterator Stco=Stream->second.stco.begin();
1466 if (Value<*Stco)
1467 return Read_Buffer_Seek(3, 0, ID);
1468
1469 for (; Stco!=Stream->second.stco.end(); ++Stco)
1470 {
1471 std::vector<int64u>::iterator Stco_Next=Stco; ++Stco_Next;
1472 if (Stco_Next!=Stream->second.stco.end() && Value>=*Stco && Value<*Stco_Next)
1473 {
1474 if (JumpTo>*Stco)
1475 JumpTo=*Stco;
1476 break;
1477 }
1478 }
1479 }
1480 break;
1481 default : ;
1482 }
1483
1484 GoTo(JumpTo);
1485 Open_Buffer_Unsynch();
1486 return 1;
1487 }
1488 case 1 :
1489 if (Value==0)
1490 return Read_Buffer_Seek(3, 0, ID);
1491
1492 if (FirstMoovPos==(int64u)-1)
1493 return 6; //Internal error
1494
1495 return Read_Buffer_Seek(0, FirstMdatPos+(LastMdatPos-FirstMdatPos)*Value/10000, ID);
1496 case 2 : //Timestamp
1497 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1498 {
1499 //Searching time stamp offset due to Time code offset
1500 for (std::map<int32u, stream>::iterator Stream=Streams.begin(); Stream!=Streams.end(); ++Stream)
1501 if (Stream->second.StreamKind==Stream_Video)
1502 {
1503 if (Value>TimeCode_DtsOffset) //Removing Time Code offset
1504 Value-=TimeCode_DtsOffset;
1505 else
1506 Value=0; //Sooner
1507 break;
1508 }
1509
1510 //Looking for the minimal stream offset, for every video/audio/text stream
1511 int64u JumpTo=File_Size;
1512 for (std::map<int32u, stream>::iterator Stream=Streams.begin(); Stream!=Streams.end(); ++Stream)
1513 switch (Stream->second.StreamKind)
1514 {
1515 case Stream_Video :
1516 case Stream_Audio :
1517 case Stream_Text :
1518 {
1519 int64u Value2=float64_int64s(((float64)Value)*Stream->second.mdhd_TimeScale/1000000000); //Transformed in mpeg4 ticks (per track)
1520
1521 //Searching the corresponding frame
1522 for (stream::stts_durations::iterator stts_Duration=Stream->second.stts_Durations.begin(); stts_Duration!=Stream->second.stts_Durations.end(); ++stts_Duration)
1523 {
1524 if (Value2>=stts_Duration->DTS_Begin && Value2<stts_Duration->DTS_End)
1525 {
1526 int64u FrameNumber=stts_Duration->Pos_Begin+(Value2-stts_Duration->DTS_Begin)/stts_Duration->SampleDuration;
1527
1528 //Searching the I-Frame
1529 if (!Stream->second.stss.empty())
1530 {
1531 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<Stream->second.stss.size(); Pos++)
1532 if (FrameNumber<=Stream->second.stss[Pos])
1533 {
1534 if (Pos && FrameNumber<Stream->second.stss[Pos])
1535 FrameNumber=Stream->second.stss[Pos-1];
1536 break;
1537 }
1538 }
1539
1540 //Searching the corresponding stco
1541 std::vector<stream::stsc_struct>::iterator Stsc=Stream->second.stsc.begin();
1542 int64u SamplePos=0;
1543 for (; Stsc!=Stream->second.stsc.end(); ++Stsc)
1544 {
1545 std::vector<stream::stsc_struct>::iterator Stsc_Next=Stsc; ++Stsc_Next;
1546 int64u CountOfSamples = ((Stsc_Next == Stream->second.stsc.end() ? (int64u)Stream->second.stco.size() : (int64u)Stsc_Next->FirstChunk) - (int64u)Stsc->FirstChunk) * (int64u)Stsc->SamplesPerChunk;
1547 if (Stsc_Next!=Stream->second.stsc.end() && FrameNumber>=SamplePos+CountOfSamples)
1548 SamplePos+=CountOfSamples;
1549 else
1550 {
1551 int64u CountOfChunks=(FrameNumber-SamplePos)/Stsc->SamplesPerChunk;
1552 size_t stco_Pos=(size_t)(Stsc->FirstChunk-1+CountOfChunks); //-1 because first chunk is number 1
1553 if (stco_Pos>Stream->second.stco.size())
1554 return 2; //Invalid FrameNumber
1555 if (JumpTo>Stream->second.stco[stco_Pos])
1556 JumpTo=Stream->second.stco[stco_Pos];
1557 break;
1558 }
1559 }
1560
1561 }
1562 }
1563
1564 }
1565 break;
1566 default : ;
1567 }
1568
1569 if (!StreamOffset_Jump.empty())
1570 {
1571 std::map<int64u, int64u>::iterator StreamOffset_Current=StreamOffset_Jump.end();
1572 do
1573 --StreamOffset_Current;
1574 while (StreamOffset_Current->second>JumpTo && StreamOffset_Current!=StreamOffset_Jump.begin());
1575 JumpTo=StreamOffset_Current->second;
1576 }
1577
1578 GoTo(JumpTo);
1579 Open_Buffer_Unsynch();
1580 return 1;
1581 }
1582 #else //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1583 return (size_t)-1; //Not supported
1584 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1585 case 3 :
1586 //FrameNumber
1587 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1588 {
1589 //Looking for video stream
1590 std::map<int32u, stream>::iterator Stream;
1591 for (Stream=Streams.begin(); Stream!=Streams.end(); ++Stream)
1592 if (Stream->second.StreamKind==Stream_Video)
1593 break;
1594 if (Stream==Streams.end())
1595 for (Stream=Streams.begin(); Stream!=Streams.end(); ++Stream)
1596 if (Stream->second.StreamKind==Stream_Audio)
1597 break;
1598 if (Stream==Streams.end())
1599 for (Stream=Streams.begin(); Stream!=Streams.end(); ++Stream)
1600 if (Stream->second.StreamKind==Stream_Text)
1601 break;
1602 if (Stream==Streams.end())
1603 return 0; //Not supported
1604
1605 //Searching the I-Frame
1606 if (!Stream->second.stss.empty())
1607 {
1608 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<Stream->second.stss.size(); Pos++)
1609 if (Value<=Stream->second.stss[Pos])
1610 {
1611 if (Pos && Value<Stream->second.stss[Pos])
1612 Value=Stream->second.stss[Pos-1];
1613 break;
1614 }
1615 }
1616
1617 //Searching the corresponding stco
1618 std::vector<stream::stsc_struct>::iterator Stsc=Stream->second.stsc.begin();
1619 int64u SamplePos=0;
1620 for (; Stsc!=Stream->second.stsc.end(); ++Stsc)
1621 {
1622 std::vector<stream::stsc_struct>::iterator Stsc_Next=Stsc; ++Stsc_Next;
1623 int64u CountOfSamples = ((Stsc_Next == Stream->second.stsc.end() ? ((int64u)Stream->second.stco.size()) : ((int64u)Stsc_Next->FirstChunk)) - (int64u)Stsc->FirstChunk) * (int64u)Stsc->SamplesPerChunk;
1624 if (Stsc_Next!=Stream->second.stsc.end() && Value>=SamplePos+CountOfSamples)
1625 SamplePos+=CountOfSamples;
1626 else
1627 {
1628 int64u CountOfChunks=(Value-SamplePos)/Stsc->SamplesPerChunk;
1629 size_t stco_Pos=(size_t)(Stsc->FirstChunk-1+CountOfChunks); //-1 because first chunk is number 1
1630 if (stco_Pos>Stream->second.stco.size())
1631 return 2; //Invalid value
1632 int64u Offset=Stream->second.stco[stco_Pos];
1633
1634 //Seeking back to audio/text frames before this video frame
1635 if (!StreamOffset_Jump.empty())
1636 {
1637 if (stco_Pos==0) //The first Stco is considered as the last byte of previous stram
1638 {
1639 if (!mdat_Pos.empty())
1640 Offset=mdat_Pos[0].Offset;
1641 }
1642 else
1643 {
1644 std::map<int64u, int64u>::iterator StreamOffset_Jump_Temp=StreamOffset_Jump.find(Stream->second.stco[stco_Pos]);
1645 if (StreamOffset_Jump_Temp!=StreamOffset_Jump.end())
1646 Offset=StreamOffset_Jump_Temp->second;
1647 }
1648 }
1649 else
1650 {
1651 //TODO
1652 }
1653
1654 GoTo(Offset);
1655 Open_Buffer_Unsynch();
1656 return 1;
1657 }
1658 }
1659
1660 return 2; //Invalid value
1661 }
1662 #else //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1663 return (size_t)-1; //Not supported
1664 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1665 default : return 0;
1666 }
1667}
1668#endif //MEDIAINFO_SEEK

1685//***************************************************************************
1686// Buffer
1687//***************************************************************************
1688
1689//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1690bool File_Mpeg4::Header_Begin()
1691{
1692 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1693 //Handling of multiple frames in one block
1694 if (IsParsing_mdat && Config->Demux_Unpacketize_Get())
1695 {
1696 stream &Stream_Temp=Streams[(int32u)Element_Code];
1697 if (Stream_Temp.Demux_EventWasSent)
1698 {
1699 Open_Buffer_Continue(Stream_Temp.Parsers[0], Buffer+Buffer_Offset, 0);
1700 if (Config->Demux_EventWasSent)
1701 return false;
1702 Stream_Temp.Demux_EventWasSent=false;
1703 }
1704 }
1705 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1706
1707 if (IsParsing_mdat && Element_Level==0)
1708 Element_Begin0();
1709
1710 return true;
1711}
1712
1713//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1714void File_Mpeg4::Header_Parse()
1715{
1716 //mdat
1717 if (IsParsing_mdat)
1718 {
1719 //Positionning
1720 if (mdat_Pos_Temp==mdat_Pos_Max || File_Offset+Buffer_Offset<mdat_Pos_Temp->Offset)
1721 {
1722 Header_Fill_Code(0, "(Junk)");
1723 int64u Size=mdat_Pos_Temp==mdat_Pos_Max?Element_TotalSize_Get():(mdat_Pos_Temp->Offset-(File_Offset+Buffer_Offset));
1724 if (Size>1 && Size>=Buffer_MaximumSize/2)
1725 Size=Buffer_MaximumSize;
1726 if (Size==Element_TotalSize_Get())
1727 IsParsing_mdat=false;
1728 Header_Fill_Size(Size);
1729 return;
1730 }
1731
1732 //Filling
1733 Header_Fill_Code2(mdat_Pos_Temp->StreamID, Ztring::ToZtring(mdat_Pos_Temp->StreamID));
1734 Header_Fill_Size(mdat_Pos_Temp->Size);
1735 if (Buffer_Offset+mdat_Pos_Temp->Size<=Buffer_Size) //Only if we will not need it later (in case of partial data, this function will be called again for the same chunk)
1736 {
1737 mdat_Pos_Temp++;
1738 while (mdat_Pos_Temp!=mdat_Pos_Max)
1739 {
1740 if (mdat_Pos_NormalParsing && !Streams[mdat_Pos_Temp->StreamID].IsPriorityStream)
1741 break;
1742 if (!mdat_Pos_NormalParsing && Streams[mdat_Pos_Temp->StreamID].IsPriorityStream)
1743 break;
1744 mdat_Pos_Temp++;
1745 }
1746 }
1747 else
1748 Element_WaitForMoreData();
1749
1750 //Hints
1751 if (File_Buffer_Size_Hint_Pointer && mdat_Pos_Temp!=mdat_Pos_Max && mdat_Pos_Temp->Offset+mdat_Pos_Temp->Size>File_Offset+Buffer_Size && mdat_Pos_Temp->Offset<File_Offset+Buffer_Size+128*1024)
1752 {
1753 size_t Buffer_Size_Target=(size_t)(mdat_Pos_Temp->Offset+mdat_Pos_Temp->Size-(File_Offset+Buffer_Size));
1754 if (Buffer_Size_Target<128*1024)
1755 Buffer_Size_Target=128*1024;
1756 (*File_Buffer_Size_Hint_Pointer)=Buffer_Size_Target;
1757 }
1758
1759 return;
1760 }
1761
1762 //Parsing
1763 int64u Size;
1764 int32u Size_32, Name;
1765 if (Element_Size==2)
1766 {
1767 if (!Element_IsComplete_Get())
1768 {
1769 Element_WaitForMoreData();
1770 return;
1771 }
1772
1773 int16u Size_16;
1774 Peek_B2(Size_16);
1775 if (!Size_16)
1776 {
1777 Skip_B2( "Size");
1778
1779 //Filling
1780 Header_Fill_Code(0, "Junk");
1781 Header_Fill_Size(2);
1782 return;
1783 }
1784 }
1785 Get_B4 (Size_32, "Size");
1786 if (Size_32==0 && (Element_Size==4 || Element_Size==8))
1787 {
1788 if (!Element_IsComplete_Get())
1789 {
1790 Element_WaitForMoreData();
1791 return;
1792 }
1793
1794 //Filling
1795 Header_Fill_Code(0, "Junk");
1796 Header_Fill_Size(4);
1797 return;
1798 }
1799 Size=Size_32;
1800 Get_C4 (Name, "Name");
1801 if (Name==0x33647666) //3dvf
1802 Name=0x6D6F6F76; //moov
1803 if (Name==0x61766964) //avid
1804 Name=0x6D646174; //mdat
1805
1806 if (Size<8)
1807 {
1808 //Special case: until the end of the atom
1809 if (Size==0)
1810 {
1811 Size=Config->File_Current_Size-(File_Offset+Buffer_Offset);
1812 if (Status[IsAccepted] && Element_Level==2 && Name==0x00000000) //First real level (Level 1 is atom, level 2 is header block)
1813 {
1814 Element_Offset=0;
1815 Name=Elements::mdat;
1816 }
1817 }
1818 //Special case: Big files, size is 64-bit
1819 else if (Size==1)
1820 {
1821 //Reading Extended size
1822 Get_B8 (Size, "Size (Extended)");
1823 }
1824 //Not in specs!
1825 else
1826 {
1827 Size=Config->File_Current_Size-(File_Offset+Buffer_Offset);
1828 }
1829 }
1830
1831 //Specific case: file begin with "free" atom
1832 if (!Status[IsAccepted]
1833 && (Name==Elements::free
1834 || Name==Elements::skip
1835 || Name==Elements::wide))
1836 {
1837 Accept("MPEG-4");
1838 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_Format, "QuickTime");
1839 }
1840
1841 //Filling
1842 Header_Fill_Code(Name, Ztring().From_CC4(Name));
1843 Header_Fill_Size(Size);
1844
1845 if (Name==0x6D6F6F76 && Buffer_Offset+Size>Buffer_Size-Buffer_Offset) //moov
1846 {
1847 File_Buffer_Size_Hint_Pointer=Config->File_Buffer_Size_Hint_Pointer_Get();
1848
1849 //Hints
1850 if (File_Buffer_Size_Hint_Pointer && Size>128*1024)
1851 {
1852 size_t Buffer_Size_Target=(size_t)(Buffer_Offset+Size-(Buffer_Size-Buffer_Offset));
1853 if (Buffer_Size_Target<128*1024)
1854 Buffer_Size_Target=128*1024;
1855 (*File_Buffer_Size_Hint_Pointer)=Buffer_Size_Target;
1856 }
1857 }
1858
1859 //Incoherencies
1860 if (Element_Level<=2 && File_Offset+Buffer_Offset+Size>File_Size)
1861 Fill(Stream_General, 0, "IsTruncated", "Yes");
1862}
1863
1864//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1865struct Mpeg4_muxing
1866{
1867 int64u MinimalOffset;
1868 int64u MaximalOffset;
1869
1870 Mpeg4_muxing()
1871 {
1872 MinimalOffset=(int64u)-1;
1873 MaximalOffset=0;
1874 }
1875};
1876bool File_Mpeg4::BookMark_Needed()
1877{
1878 #if MEDIAINFO_HASH
1879 if (!mdat_MustParse && !mdat_Pos_NormalParsing && Config->File_Hash_Get().to_ulong() && FirstMdatPos<FirstMoovPos)
1880 {
1881 Element_Show();
1882 while (Element_Level>0)
1883 Element_End0();
1884 mdat_Pos_NormalParsing=true;
1885 GoTo(0);
1886 IsSecondPass=true;
1887 return false;
1888 }
1889 #endif //MEDIAINFO_HASH
1890
1891 if (!mdat_MustParse)
1892 return false;
1893
1894 //Handling of some wrong stsz and stsc atoms (ADPCM)
1895 if (!IsSecondPass)
1896 for (std::map<int32u, stream>::iterator Temp=Streams.begin(); Temp!=Streams.end(); ++Temp)
1897 if (Temp->second.StreamKind==Stream_Audio
1898 && (Retrieve(Stream_Audio, Temp->second.StreamPos, Audio_CodecID)==__T("ima4")
1899 || Retrieve(Stream_Audio, Temp->second.StreamPos, Audio_CodecID)==__T("11")))
1900 {
1901 Temp->second.stsz_StreamSize/=16;
1902 Temp->second.stsz_StreamSize*=17;
1903 float32 BitRate_Nominal=Retrieve(Stream_Audio, Temp->second.StreamPos, Audio_BitRate_Nominal).To_float32();
1904 if (BitRate_Nominal)
1905 {
1906 BitRate_Nominal/=16;
1907 BitRate_Nominal*=17;
1908 Fill(Stream_Audio, Temp->second.StreamPos, Audio_BitRate_Nominal, BitRate_Nominal, 0, true);
1909 }
1910 int64u Channels=Retrieve(Stream_Audio, Temp->second.StreamPos, Audio_Channel_s_).To_int64u();
1911 if (Channels!=2)
1912 {
1913 Temp->second.stsz_StreamSize/=2;
1914 Temp->second.stsz_StreamSize*=Channels;
1915 }
1916 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<Temp->second.stsc.size(); Pos++)
1917 {
1918 Temp->second.stsc[Pos].SamplesPerChunk/=16;
1919 Temp->second.stsc[Pos].SamplesPerChunk*=17;
1920 if (Channels!=2)
1921 {
1922 Temp->second.stsc[Pos].SamplesPerChunk/=2;
1923 Temp->second.stsc[Pos].SamplesPerChunk*=(int32u)Channels;
1924 }
1925 }
1926 }
1927
1928 //In case of second pass
1929 if (mdat_Pos.empty())
1930 {
1931 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1932 std::map<int32u, struct Mpeg4_muxing> Muxing; //key is StreamID
1933 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1934 size_t stco_Count=(size_t)-1;
1935 bool stco_IsDifferent=false;
1936
1937 //For each stream
1938 for (std::map<int32u, stream>::iterator Temp=Streams.begin(); Temp!=Streams.end(); ++Temp)
1939 if (!Temp->second.Parsers.empty())
1940 {
1941 if (!Temp->second.File_Name.empty())
1942 {
1943 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1944 if (Config_Demux && Config->File_Demux_Interleave_Get()
1945 && Temp->second.StreamKind!=Stream_Other) // e.g. a time code, we can live without demuxing the time code
1946 {
1947 //Remark: supporting both embedded and referenced streams is currently not supported
1948 mdat_Pos.clear();
1949 return false;
1950 }
1951 else
1952 #endif // MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1953 continue;
1954 }
1955
1956 if (!Temp->second.stsz.empty() || Temp->second.stsz_Sample_Size)
1957 {
1958 if (!stco_IsDifferent)
1959 {
1960 if (stco_Count==(size_t)-1)
1961 stco_Count=Temp->second.stco.size();
1962 else if (stco_Count!=Temp->second.stco.size())
1963 stco_IsDifferent=true;
1964 }
1965
1966 size_t Chunk_FrameCount=0;
1967 int32u Chunk_Number=1;
1968 int32u Sample_ByteSize=0;
1969 if (Temp->second.StreamKind==Stream_Audio)
1970 Sample_ByteSize=Retrieve(Stream_Audio, Temp->second.StreamPos, Audio_BitDepth).To_int32u()*Retrieve(Stream_Audio, Temp->second.StreamPos, Audio_Channel_s_).To_int32u()/8;
1971
1972 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1973 stream::stts_durations Temp_stts_Durations;
1974 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1975 if (!Temp->second.stco.empty() && !Temp->second.stsc.empty())
1976 {
1977 int64u* stco_Current = &Temp->second.stco[0];
1978 int64u* stco_Max = stco_Current + Temp->second.stco.size();
1979 int64u* stsz_Current = Temp->second.stsz.empty()?NULL:&Temp->second.stsz[0];
1980 int64u* stsz_Max = stsz_Current + Temp->second.stsz.size();
1981 stream::stsc_struct* stsc_Current = &Temp->second.stsc[0];
1982 stream::stsc_struct* stsc_Max = stsc_Current + Temp->second.stsc.size();
1983 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1984 int64u MinimalOffset = (int64u)-1;
1985 int64u MaximalOffset = 0;
1986 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1987 for (; stco_Current<stco_Max; ++stco_Current)
1988 {
1989 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1990 if (MinimalOffset>*stco_Current)
1991 MinimalOffset = *stco_Current;
1992 if (MaximalOffset < *stco_Current)
1993 MaximalOffset = *stco_Current;
1994 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1995
1996 while (stsc_Current + 1 < stsc_Max && Chunk_Number >= (stsc_Current + 1)->FirstChunk)
1997 stsc_Current++;
1998
1999 if (Temp->second.stsz_Sample_Size == 0 && stsc_Current && !Temp->second.stsz.empty())
2000 {
2001 //Each sample has its own size
2002 int64u Chunk_Offset = 0;
2003 for (size_t Pos = 0; Pos < stsc_Current->SamplesPerChunk; Pos++)
2004 if (*stsz_Current)
2005 {
2006 mdat_Pos_Type mdat_Pos_Temp2;
2007 mdat_Pos_Temp2.Offset = *stco_Current + Chunk_Offset;
2008 mdat_Pos_Temp2.StreamID = Temp->first;
2009 mdat_Pos_Temp2.Size = *stsz_Current;
2010 mdat_Pos.push_back(mdat_Pos_Temp2);
2011 Chunk_Offset += *stsz_Current;
2012 stsz_Current++;
2013 if (stsz_Current >= stsz_Max)
2014 break;
2015 }
2016 if (stsz_Current >= stsz_Max)
2017 break;
2018 }
2019 else if (Temp->second.IsPcm && (!Sample_ByteSize || Temp->second.stsz_Sample_Size <= Sample_ByteSize) && stsc_Current && stsc_Current->SamplesPerChunk*Temp->second.stsz_Sample_Size*Temp->second.stsz_Sample_Multiplier < 0x1000000)
2020 {
2021 //Same size per sample, but granularity is too small
2022 mdat_Pos_Type mdat_Pos_Temp2;
2023 mdat_Pos_Temp2.Offset = *stco_Current;
2024 mdat_Pos_Temp2.StreamID = Temp->first;
2025 mdat_Pos_Temp2.Size = stsc_Current->SamplesPerChunk*Temp->second.stsz_Sample_Size*Temp->second.stsz_Sample_Multiplier;
2026 mdat_Pos.push_back(mdat_Pos_Temp2);
2027
2028 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
2029 if (Temp_stts_Durations.empty() || stsc_Current->SamplesPerChunk != Temp_stts_Durations[Temp_stts_Durations.size() - 1].SampleDuration)
2030 {
2031 stream::stts_duration stts_Duration;
2032 stts_Duration.Pos_Begin = Temp_stts_Durations.empty() ? 0 : Temp_stts_Durations[Temp_stts_Durations.size() - 1].Pos_End;
2033 stts_Duration.Pos_End = stts_Duration.Pos_Begin + 1;
2034 stts_Duration.SampleDuration = stsc_Current->SamplesPerChunk;
2035 stts_Duration.DTS_Begin = Temp_stts_Durations.empty() ? 0 : Temp_stts_Durations[Temp_stts_Durations.size() - 1].DTS_End;
2036 stts_Duration.DTS_End = stts_Duration.DTS_Begin + stts_Duration.SampleDuration;
2037 Temp_stts_Durations.push_back(stts_Duration);
2038 //Temp->second.stsc[stsc_Pos].SamplesPerChunk=1;
2039 }
2040 else
2041 {
2042 Temp_stts_Durations[Temp_stts_Durations.size() - 1].Pos_End++;
2043 Temp_stts_Durations[Temp_stts_Durations.size() - 1].DTS_End += Temp_stts_Durations[Temp_stts_Durations.size() - 1].SampleDuration;
2044 }
2045 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
2046 }
2047 else if (stsc_Current < stsc_Max && stsc_Current->SamplesPerChunk*Temp->second.stsz_Sample_Size < File_Size) // Checking integrity. TODO: don't try to expand the samples, just use data directly
2048 {
2049 //Same size per sample
2050 int64u Chunk_Offset = 0;
2051 for (size_t Pos = 0; Pos < stsc_Current->SamplesPerChunk; Pos++)
2052 if (Temp->second.stsz_Sample_Size*Temp->second.stsz_Sample_Multiplier)
2053 {
2054 int64u Size = Temp->second.stsz_Sample_Size*Temp->second.stsz_Sample_Multiplier;
2055 mdat_Pos_Type mdat_Pos_Temp2;
2056 mdat_Pos_Temp2.Offset = *stco_Current + Chunk_Offset;
2057 mdat_Pos_Temp2.StreamID = Temp->first;
2058 mdat_Pos_Temp2.Size = Size;
2059 mdat_Pos.push_back(mdat_Pos_Temp2);
2060 Chunk_Offset += Size;
2061 Chunk_FrameCount++;
2062 }
2063 if (Chunk_FrameCount >= FrameCount_MaxPerStream)
2064 break;
2065 }
2066
2067 Chunk_Number++;
2068 }
2069 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
2070 Muxing[Temp->first].MinimalOffset=MinimalOffset;
2071 Muxing[Temp->first].MaximalOffset=MaximalOffset;
2072 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
2073 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<Temp->second.Parsers.size(); Pos++)
2074 Temp->second.Parsers[Pos]->Stream_BitRateFromContainer=Temp->second.stsz_StreamSize*8/(((float64)Temp->second.stts_Duration)/Temp->second.mdhd_TimeScale);
2075 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
2076 if (FrameCount_MaxPerStream==(int32u)-1 && !Temp_stts_Durations.empty())
2077 {
2078 Temp->second.stts_Durations=Temp_stts_Durations;
2079 for (stsc_Current=&Temp->second.stsc[0]; stsc_Current<stsc_Max; ++stsc_Current)
2080 stsc_Current->SamplesPerChunk=1;
2081 Temp->second.stts_FrameCount=Temp_stts_Durations[Temp_stts_Durations.size()-1].Pos_End;
2082 }
2083 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
2084 }
2085 }
2086
2087 //special cases
2088 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
2089 if (Temp->second.stsz.empty() && Temp->second.StreamKind==Stream_Video && Retrieve(Stream_Video, Temp->second.StreamPos, Video_CodecID)==__T("AV1x"))
2090 {
2091 //Found unknown data before the raw content
2092 int64u Width=Retrieve(Stream_Video, Temp->second.StreamPos, Video_Width).To_int64u();
2093 int64u Height=Retrieve(Stream_Video, Temp->second.StreamPos, Video_Height).To_int64u();
2094 if (Width && Height && Temp->second.stsz_Sample_Size>(Width*Height*2))
2095 Temp->second.Demux_Offset=Temp->second.stsz_Sample_Size-(Width*Height*2); // YUV 4:2:2 8 bit = 2 bytes per pixel
2096 }
2097 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
2098 }
2099 std::sort(mdat_Pos.begin(), mdat_Pos.end(), &mdat_pos_sort);
2100 mdat_Pos_Temp=mdat_Pos.empty()?NULL:&mdat_Pos[0];
2101 mdat_Pos_Max=mdat_Pos_Temp+mdat_Pos.size();
2102
2103 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
2104 if (!stco_IsDifferent && Muxing.size()==2)
2105 {
2106 std::map<int32u, struct Mpeg4_muxing>::iterator Muxing_1=Muxing.begin();
2107 std::map<int32u, struct Mpeg4_muxing>::iterator Muxing_2=Muxing.begin(); ++Muxing_2;
2108 if (Muxing_1->second.MaximalOffset>Muxing_2->second.MinimalOffset)
2109 swap(Muxing_1, Muxing_2);
2110 if (Muxing_1->second.MaximalOffset<=Muxing_2->second.MinimalOffset)
2111 {
2112 for (size_t stco_Pos=1; stco_Pos<stco_Count; stco_Pos++)
2113 {
2114 StreamOffset_Jump[Streams[Muxing_1->first].stco[stco_Pos]]=Streams[Muxing_2->first].stco[stco_Pos-1];
2115 StreamOffset_Jump[Streams[Muxing_2->first].stco[stco_Pos]]=Streams[Muxing_1->first].stco[stco_Pos];
2116 }
2117 StreamOffset_Jump[Streams[Muxing_2->first].stco[0]]=Streams[Muxing_2->first].stco[stco_Count-1];
2118 }
2119 }
2120 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
2121 }
2122 if (mdat_Pos.empty())
2123 return false;
2124
2125 IsParsing_mdat=false;
2126 if (!mdat_Pos_ToParseInPriority_StreamIDs.empty())
2127 {
2128 //Hanlding StreamIDs to parse in priority (currently, only the first block of each stream is parsed in priority)
2129 if (!Streams[mdat_Pos_ToParseInPriority_StreamIDs[0]].stco.empty())
2130 {
2131 mdat_Pos_Type* Temp=&mdat_Pos[0];
2132 int64u stco_ToFind=Streams[mdat_Pos_ToParseInPriority_StreamIDs[0]].stco[0];
2133 while (Temp<mdat_Pos_Max && Temp->Offset!=stco_ToFind)
2134 Temp++;
2135 if (Temp<mdat_Pos_Max && Temp->Offset<File_Size) //Skipping data not in a truncated file
2136 {
2137 Element_Show();
2138 while (Element_Level>0)
2139 Element_End0();
2140 Element_Begin1("Priority streams");
2141
2142 mdat_Pos_Temp=Temp;
2143 GoTo(Temp->Offset);
2144 IsParsing_mdat=true;
2145 }
2146 }
2147 mdat_Pos_ToParseInPriority_StreamIDs.erase(mdat_Pos_ToParseInPriority_StreamIDs.begin());
2148 }
2149
2150 if (File_GoTo==(int64u)-1 && !mdat_Pos_NormalParsing && !mdat_Pos.empty() && mdat_Pos.begin()->Offset<File_Size) //Skipping data not in a truncated file
2151 {
2152 Element_Show();
2153 while (Element_Level>0)
2154 Element_End0();
2155 Element_Begin1("Second pass");
2156 Element_ThisIsAList();
2157
2158 mdat_Pos_Temp=&mdat_Pos[0];
2159 #if MEDIAINFO_HASH
2160 if (Config->File_Hash_Get().to_ulong())
2161 {
2162 GoTo(0);
2163 Hash_ParseUpTo=mdat_Pos_Temp->Offset;
2164 }
2165 else
2166 #endif //MEDIAINFO_HASH
2167 GoTo(mdat_Pos_Temp->Offset);
2168 IsParsing_mdat=true;
2169 mdat_Pos_NormalParsing=true;
2170 }
2171
2172 IsSecondPass=true;
2173 return false; //We do not want to use the bookmark feature, only detect the end of the file
2174}

2177//Get language string from 2CC
2178Ztring File_Mpeg4::Language_Get(int16u Language)
2179{
2180 if (Language==0x7FFF || Language==0xFFFF)
2181 return Ztring();
2182
2183 if (Language<0x100)
2184 return Mpeg4_Language_Apple(Language);
2185
2186 Ztring ToReturn;
2187 ToReturn.append(1, (Char)((Language>>10&0x1F)+0x60));
2188 ToReturn.append(1, (Char)((Language>> 5&0x1F)+0x60));
2189 ToReturn.append(1, (Char)((Language>> 0&0x1F)+0x60));
2190 return ToReturn;
2191}

2333//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
2334void File_Mpeg4::Descriptors()
2335{
2336 //Preparing
2337 File_Mpeg4_Descriptors MI;
2338 MI.KindOfStream=StreamKind_Last;
2339 MI.PosOfStream=StreamPos_Last;
2340 MI.Parser_DoNotFreeIt=true;
2341
2342 int64u Elemen_Code_Save=Element_Code;
2343 Element_Code=moov_trak_tkhd_TrackID; //Element_Code is use for stream identifier
2344 Open_Buffer_Init(&MI);
2345 Element_Code=Elemen_Code_Save;
2346 mdat_MustParse=true; //Data is in MDAT
2347
2348 //Parsing
2349 Open_Buffer_Continue(&MI);
2350
2351 //Filling
2352 Finish(&MI);
2353 Merge(MI, StreamKind_Last, 0, StreamPos_Last);
2354
2355 //Special case: AAC
2356 if (StreamKind_Last==Stream_Audio
2357 && (Retrieve(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_Format)==__T("AAC")
2358 || Retrieve(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_Format)==__T("MPEG Audio")
2359 || Retrieve(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_Format)==__T("Vorbis")))
2360 Clear(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_BitDepth); //Resolution is not valid for AAC / MPEG Audio / Vorbis
2361
2362 //Parser from Descriptor
2363 if (MI.Parser)
2364 {
2365 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<Streams[moov_trak_tkhd_TrackID].Parsers.size(); Pos++)
2366 delete Streams[moov_trak_tkhd_TrackID].Parsers[Pos];
2367 Streams[moov_trak_tkhd_TrackID].Parsers.clear();
2368 Streams[moov_trak_tkhd_TrackID].Parsers.push_back(MI.Parser);
2369 mdat_MustParse=true;
2370 }
2371}

2373//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
2374void File_Mpeg4::TimeCode_Associate(int32u TrackID)
2375{
2376 //Trying to detect time code attached to 1 video only but for all streams in reality
2377 int32u TimeCode_TrackID=(int32u)-1;
2378 bool TimeCode_TrackID_MoreThanOne=false;
2379 for (std::map<int32u, stream>::iterator Strea=Streams.begin(); Strea!=Streams.end(); ++Strea)
2380 if (Strea->second.TimeCode_TrackID!=(int32u)-1)
2381 {
2382 if (TimeCode_TrackID==(int32u)-1)
2383 TimeCode_TrackID=Strea->second.TimeCode_TrackID;
2384 else
2385 TimeCode_TrackID_MoreThanOne=true;
2386 }
2387 if (!TimeCode_TrackID_MoreThanOne && TimeCode_TrackID!=(int32u)-1)
2388 for (std::map<int32u, stream>::iterator Strea=Streams.begin(); Strea!=Streams.end(); ++Strea)
2389 Strea->second.TimeCode_TrackID=TimeCode_TrackID; //For all tracks actually
2390
2391 //Is it general or for a specific stream?
2392 bool IsGeneral=true;
2393 for (std::map<int32u, stream>::iterator Strea=Streams.begin(); Strea!=Streams.end(); ++Strea)
2394 if (Strea->second.TimeCode_TrackID==TrackID)
2395 IsGeneral=false;
2396
2397 //For each track in the file (but only the last one will be used!)
2398 for (std::map<int32u, stream>::iterator Strea=Streams.begin(); Strea!=Streams.end(); ++Strea)
2399 if (!Streams[TrackID].Parsers.empty() && (IsGeneral && Strea->second.StreamKind!=Stream_Max) || Strea->second.TimeCode_TrackID==TrackID)
2400 {
2401 if (Strea->second.StreamKind==Stream_Video)
2402 {
2403 Fill(Stream_Video, Strea->second.StreamPos, Video_Delay_Settings, Ztring(__T("DropFrame="))+(Streams[TrackID].TimeCode->DropFrame?__T("Yes"):__T("No")));
2404 Fill(Stream_Video, Strea->second.StreamPos, Video_Delay_Settings, Ztring(__T("24HourMax="))+(Streams[TrackID].TimeCode->H24?__T("Yes"):__T("No")));
2405 Fill(Stream_Video, Strea->second.StreamPos, Video_Delay_Settings, Ztring(__T("IsVisual="))+(Streams[TrackID].TimeCode_IsVisual?__T("Yes"):__T("No")));
2406 }
2407 if (Strea->second.StreamKind!=Stream_Other)
2408 {
2409 Fill(Strea->second.StreamKind, Strea->second.StreamPos, "Delay", Streams[TrackID].Parsers[0]->Get(Stream_General, 0, "Delay"));
2410 Fill(Strea->second.StreamKind, Strea->second.StreamPos, "Delay_DropFrame", Streams[TrackID].TimeCode->DropFrame?__T("Yes"):__T("No"));
2411 Fill(Strea->second.StreamKind, Strea->second.StreamPos, "Delay_Source", "Container");
2412 }
2413
2414 //Fill(Strea->second.StreamKind, Strea->second.StreamPos, "TimeCode_FirstFrame", Streams[TrackID].Parsers[0]->Get(Stream_General, 0, "TimeCode_FirstFrame"));
2415 //Fill(Strea->second.StreamKind, Strea->second.StreamPos, "TimeCode_Source", Streams[TrackID].Parsers[0]->Get(Stream_General, 0, "TimeCode_Source"));
2416 }
2417 }
